The results in the table above show that on average, the total estimates tend to become closer to the true value (T=2293) when the overall sample size increases. In addition, the means over domains of the estimated standard errors and coefficients of variation decrease with increasing the overall sample size. We also note that the use of auxiliary information by the GREG estimator improves accuracy when compared to the HT estimator.

The results are illustrated graphically below. For each estimator, the first graph illustrates how standard error estimates decrease with increasing sample size, for all domain sample sizes. A decrease in estimated coefficients of variation can be clearly seen in the second graph.
